title: A US state asked for evidence to ban TikTok. The FBI offered none

title: With newfound powers, statehouse Democrats race to expand voting rights
description: After strong electoral results in the midterm elections, Democrats in some key states are moving quickly this year on voting rights -- pushing ambitious plans to expand access to the ballot ahead of the 2024 presidential election.
author: Fredreka Schouten

title: Michigan Gov. Whitmer plans to enact stricter gun laws, repeal abortion restrictions, provide tax relief
description: Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer gave her State of the State address on Wednesday. She plans to enact stricter gun laws, provide immediate tax relief, and repeal abortion laws.
author: Associated Press

title: Dem-controlled Michigan Legislature approves $1B spending plan
description: The Michigan Legislature approved Thursday night a spending package amounting to $1.1 billion for industry and the state's economic development fund.
author: Associated Press

title: Some Democrats are worried about Harris’s political prospects
description: In interviews, more than a dozen Democratic leaders and activists expressed misgivings about Kamala Harris at the top of the Democratic Party.

title: Republican governor makes strong accusation against Ford — and it could help Michigan
description: It's bad business to nix deals that can create jobs just because they may involve Chinese companies, argued ex-Michigan Gov. Rick Snyder.

title: Michigan Senate OKs earlier presidential primary, to dismay of GOP
description: Republicans say the move violates national party rules, resulting in less power for the state in choosing the GOP presidential nominee in 2024.
